%S A393983 1,18,864,55152,4035906,320012532,26749991016,2321220412368,
%T A393983 207113986857024,18882911163871872,1751433553924329600,
%U A393983 164743357888569358080,15677768071123387997040,1506728474191313049690720,146030351004313771119428160,14256607797751707815942160000
%N A393983 a(n) = 108^n * [z^n] hypergeom([1/6, 1/3], [1], z)^3.
%C A393983 Symmetric-cube coefficients of the Gauss hypergeometric series at the mixed CM point (1/6,1/3;1).
%C A393983 The sequence has a level-3 modular realization. Let u = eta(3*tau)^12/eta(tau)^12, t = u/(1+27*u)^2, C0 = 3*E_{5,chi_0,chi_3}, and Cmix = (1-27*u)*C0 = 3*E_{5,chi_0,chi_3} - 27*E_{5,chi_3,chi_0}. Then a(n) = [q^n] Cmix(q)*(q/t(q))^n.
%C A393983 For primes p >= 7 with p == 1 (mod 3), the cited preprint proves the unconditional scalar congruence a(p) == 18 (mod p^3). It also proves the split Eisenstein coefficient tower for Cmix.
%C A393983 Conjecturally, for primes p >= 7 with p == 1 (mod 3), a(m*p) == a(m) (mod p^4) for all m >= 1. In the cited preprint this full mod p^4 congruence is reduced to explicit Cartier/transport congruences and is verified computationally for the tested split primes; it is not claimed there as an unconditional theorem.
%D A393983 L. Long, F.-T. Tu, N. Yui, and W. Zudilin, Supercongruences for rigid hypergeometric Calabi-Yau threefolds, Adv. Math. 393 (2021), Paper No. 108058.
%H A393983 Frits Beukers, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2403.03301">Supercongruences using modular forms</a>, arXiv:2403.03301 [math.NT], 2024-2025.
%H A393983 Vaclav Kotesovec, <a href="/A393983/a393983.jpg">Graph - the asymptotic ratio (1000 terms)</a>
%H A393983 Alex Shvets, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19878741">Split-prime supercongruences at a mixed CM point: unconditional mod p^3 closure via Clausen convolution</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%F A393983 G.f.: hypergeom([1/6, 1/3], [1], 108*z)^3.
%F A393983 a(n) satisfies the order-2 recurrence (n+2)^4*a(n+2) - 6*(36*n^4 + 198*n^3 + 424*n^2 + 417*n + 158)*a(n+1) + 324*(n+1)*(2*n+1)*(3*n+2)*(6*n+5)*a(n) = 0, with a(0)=1, a(1)=18.
%F A393983 a(n) ~ Gamma(1/3)^3 * 2^(2*n - 13/3) * 3^(3*n + 5/2) / (Pi^(7/2) * n^(3/2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 08 2026
%e A393983 a(0) = 108^0 * [z^0] (1 + z/18 + 7*z^2/324 + ...)^3 = 1.
%e A393983 a(1) = 108 * [z^1] (1 + z/18 + 7*z^2/324 + ...)^3 = 108 * 1/6 = 18.
%e A393983 a(2) = 108^2 * [z^2] (1 + z/18 + 7*z^2/324 + ...)^3 = 11664 * 2/27 = 864.
%t A393983 CoefficientList[Series[Hypergeometric2F1[1/6, 1/3, 1, 108 z]^3, {z, 0, 15}], z]
%o A393983 (PARI) a(n) = {my(A=vector(max(n+1,2))); A[1]=1; A[2]=18; for(k=0, n-2, A[k+3] = (6*(36*k^4+198*k^3+424*k^2+417*k+158)*A[k+2] - 324*(k+1)*(2*k+1)*(3*k+2)*(6*k+5)*A[k+1])/(k+2)^4); A[n+1]}
%o A393983 (PARI) Vec(hypergeom([1/6, 1/3], [1], 108*z)^3) \\ _Michel Marcus_, May 13 2026
